arts.ttl: Pre-Match Analysis: High-flying Bournemouth face in-form Crystal Palace
arts.sum: Bournemouth have been unbeaten since their opening league fixture against Liverpool, whilst Palace come into the game off the back of their first loss; a late Jack Grealish winner for Everton ending the Eaglesâ€™ 19-game unbeaten streak. Defensively, both teams are impressive, each keeping three clean sheets and conceding under ten goals, with Palace boasting the joint-second best record with just five.
